          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Prompt neutron emission probability distribution",
                " provided by a Monte-Carlo simulation which was",
                " performed assuming",
                " - binomial distribution for the neutron multiplicity",
                "    (Gaussian distribution does not permit fitting",
                "    the data)",
                " - isotropic neutron emission in fully accelerated",
                "    fragment frames",
                " - a 20% isotropic scission component (omitting this",
                "    component does not permit fitting the data).",
                "This simulation provides adequate fitting to",
                " - the authors' measured neutron-neutron angular",
                "    correlation data",
                " - a Maxwellian fission-neutron spectrum with",
                "    kT=1.33 MeV",
                " - Skarsvag's angular correlation data between prompt",
                "    fission neutrons and light fragments."
              ]
            }
          ],
